args: The prince and friends continue their investigation\ninto the mysterious disappearances, but all of\ntheir efforts prove fruitless...
I've received a report from Albert, master.\nHe says he hasn't found even a hint\nof Yurius's current whereabouts.
Well, he can join the club, I guess;\nwe've struck out on this end as well.
Oh, hello, Astorius. We're not getting\nanywhere at the moment, but we did\nat least acquire SOMETHING useful.

We were given documents on a case
remarkably similar to oursâ€”one caused
by the seeds of the abyss over in the
Kingdom of Levin.
Levin? ...Who gave you them,\nif I might ask?
A friend of mine named Albert.
Er, is something wrong?\nYou look pale all of a sudden.
N-no, I'm fine. By Albert, might you mean\nthe famous Thunderswift Lord?
The very same. Do you know him?
By name onlyâ€”he is one of the most\nfamed heroes in all of Levin. Such men\nare far beyond my personal circle, I fear.
Regardless, I have some urgent business\nto take care of, so I must bid you farewell.
Something about this doesn't feel right.\n...Are you there, Jurota?
I have an urgent mission for you...
This way, master! Snow and Ashe\nsensed something strange over here!
I wasn't expecting to find something so\nsoon after sending Jurota. Which means...
That we're gonna catch the bad guy\nred-handed! Oh, it's gonna beâ€”WHOA!
Aw, hell. Why do a pack of fiends\nhave to decide to show up NOW?!
Wait, hang on. Do those fiends\nlook...weird to any of you?

ï¼‚Weirdï¼‚ is such an ungainly word.
These fiends were spawned by the seed,
you see, and as inheritors of its power,
will multiply as much as I desire.
And they are all powered by the people\nof this country and the mana I consumed\nfrom them! Ah ha! Aaaah ha ha ha!
You're not Astorius at all...\nYou're Yurius!
And it only took you this long to figure\nit out! Heavens above, but you are a\nSUCH a naive fool.
Still, you did prove rather open-mindedâ€”\nas one might expect from a man capable \nof forming multiple dragonpacts.
Just what are you after, Yurius?\nWhy are you wreaking havoc in my land?
I seek only to unravel the secrets of\nshapeshifting and make its power my own.
Good luck with that, pal! Everyone knows\nonly Alberian royalty can shapeshift.

Ah, but my mother came from a branch
of the Alberian royal family, which means
I have a trace amount of dragonblood
flowing in my veins.
Yet despite that, I've never been able\nto shapeshiftâ€”a fact that GREATLY\ndispleased my dear father.
He always cursed me as a failureâ€”just as\nhe did my mother, for dying while giving\nbirth to me.
I was worthless compared to true\nAlberian royalty like youâ€”but that\nwill be the case no longer!
Thanks to the device of Prince Phares,\nI have the ability to shapeshift at last!
Now, I am greater than anyoneâ€”including\nAlbert and the true dragon bloodline!
These fiends I spawned stand\nas proof of my greatness!
Aaah ha ha ha! Now, bear witness\nto the forbidden dragon of Levin!
This is MY shapeshifted formâ€”granted by\nforming a pact with a seed of the abyss!
I don't know what that thing is,\nbut it sure as hell ain't a dragon!
Yeah, and aren't seeds of the abyss\nsupposed to be fiends or something?
No, that's a dragon. A monstrous one,\nyesâ€”but a dragon all the same.
Surely your people know dragons come\nin all shapes and sizes, eh, Prince?

Before you stands a monster that does
naught but devour mana and leave death
in its wake. Albert's father was unable to
control it, and was consumed as a result.
But I will not share his fate! I CAN control\nit, and will use its power to kill all of you,\nthen Albert, then my father! Aaaah ha ha!
I understand what drove you to this...
But it's no excuse for the horrors\nthat you're planning to unleash!
Oh, and you're so certain you're right?!\nBah! Your smug sense of self-satisfaction\nand justice makes me SICK!
If you think you can judge me, then try...\nI will only learn the secrets of your power\nand make it my own!
But merely absorbing you is no funâ€”\ninstead, I will make you one with me\nand show that fool your corpse!
I can't WAIT to see how distraught\nyou will look, my dear ï¼‚heroï¼‚!
